Kowloon courier syndics suspect Iron-Wake logisticians are rerouting sealed traffic through the cathedral to evade civic audit and treaty inspection. Remove one barracks captain, one tithe-vault quartermaster, and one veinfire arsenal keeper so the smuggling chain loses its command links before the next moon ledger closes.
The audit cell confirms the covert routing chain has been interrupted at all three command nodes. Kowloon's treaty ledgers now match declared cargo flow, and Lantern Court inspectors have reopened suspended transit writs pending deeper prosecution.
